        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 1 at 6:16PM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 615 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Mason, moving northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Art, Pontotoc, Mason, Koockville, Grit, and Katemcy.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 900 PM CDT for
west central Texas.</instruction>
